results.description:
Music for the Soul invites people to gather at least once per month to share inspiration and build community through live music in a "coffeehouse" setting and occasional opportunities for singing.   The musicians will engage the "audience" in discovery and participation with the music and the audience will share their experience with each other.

Music for the Soul is part of a larger series called "Arts and Inspiration." The vision for the series is:  "Through the experience of music, visual art, film and writing and our response to its themes and questions, we will discover beauty, connect to the Spirit, build community and spread love."

On a rotating basis we will experience:
    Faith and Film: Contemporary films and discussion of themes of faith and spirit;
    Singing our Faith: Beer and Hymns and other chances to sing together;
    Artistic Spirit: Monthly gallery installation with artist and audience reflections on faith and inspiration;
    Music for the Soul Coffeehouse: performers that engages people in reflection;
    A Word of Faith: Poets and Authors offering their craft for reflection
